                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13889325" author="jahewson" created="Mon, 3 Feb 2014 08:52:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I suspect a color space issue as in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-1876&quot; title=&quot;Incorrect color for DeviceN type 4 shading object&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-1876&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-1876&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, once again I probably have a fix for this soon.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13889653" author="tilman" created="Mon, 3 Feb 2014 17:24:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There is a red edge on the top left of the circle from the radial shading example of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-615&quot; title=&quot;shfill operator needs implementation&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-615&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-615&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; that wasn&apos;t there before, and appeared after checking in a modified version of Luis&apos; code, and it is there at every resolution. (I tried a fix at the TODO segment in the code, and it worked in several files, but not on shading_patterns.pdf)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13909310" author="tilman" created="Sat, 22 Feb 2014 09:19:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Rendering result after John&apos;s refactorings. The only problem that remains (beside shadingtype 7) are the extends, i.e. the outside of the circles. This is the &quot;don&apos;t know what to do in such cases&quot; part in the code &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; (I couldn&apos;t find a solution either).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13909766" author="tilman" created="Sun, 23 Feb 2014 13:45:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I tried again fixing the bug in the radial shading and now all my test cases are fine, see attachments. Done in rev 1571009 for the trunk and 1571010 for the 1.8 branch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13909888" author="jahewson" created="Sun, 23 Feb 2014 20:50:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m getting pixelated results, see my attachment, &lt;tt&gt;GWG061_Shading_x1a1.jpg&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13909899" author="tilman" created="Sun, 23 Feb 2014 21:08:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Still getting pixelated results after the fix in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-1734&quot; title=&quot;ImageIoUtil.WriteImage doesn&amp;#39;t work with tiff images&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-1734&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-1734&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13910623" author="jahewson" created="Mon, 24 Feb 2014 18:37:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yep, its just one shading pattern which is pixelated. I tested with writing to a PNG file too to make sure it is not a JPEG issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13910723" author="tilman" created="Mon, 24 Feb 2014 19:44:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Very mysterious... it doesn&apos;t happen to me. I&apos;ll test again when I have updated to all the changes of last night (probably not today).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13912151" author="tilman" created="Tue, 25 Feb 2014 22:18:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Still getting a correct image after having updated to all the trunk changes.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13912671" author="jahewson" created="Wed, 26 Feb 2014 09:14:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Try rendering with &lt;tt&gt;-resolution 300&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13913155" author="tilman" created="Wed, 26 Feb 2014 17:01:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Still can&apos;t reproduce, not even another computer where I don&apos;t change the code. Could you check whether you have the latest version of RadialShadingContext? The question might sound silly, but I have observed that svn sometimes doesn&apos;t update code correctly.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Look &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/viewvc/pdfbox/trunk/pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdmodel/graphics/shading/RadialShadingContext.java?view=markup&amp;amp;sortby=date&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;



&lt;p&gt;And search for &quot;// both are not in the domain&quot; and compare it do your local version.&lt;br/&gt;
That part should have 4 if statements.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13913357" author="jahewson" created="Wed, 26 Feb 2014 19:17:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ok, I&apos;ve checked RadialShadingContext by hand to confirm that I have the latest version, which I do. Maybe we&apos;re getting a difference between JVMs? For me &lt;tt&gt;java -version&lt;/tt&gt; prints:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;java version &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;1.7.0_45&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
Java(TM) SE &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Runtime&lt;/span&gt; Environment (build 1.7.0_45-b18)
Java HotSpot(TM) 64-Bit Server VM (build 24.45-b08, mixed mode)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13913363" author="tilman" created="Wed, 26 Feb 2014 19:23:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have a newer one:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;java version &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;1.7.0_51&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
Java(TM) SE &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Runtime&lt;/span&gt; Environment (build 1.7.0_51-b13)
Java HotSpot(TM) 64-Bit Server VM (build 24.51-b03, mixed mode)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13913472" author="jahewson" created="Wed, 26 Feb 2014 20:36:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Well, I figured out the problem. IntelliJ is configured to run PDFBox using Java 1.6 which I also have installed, which means my Java version was actually &quot;1.6.0_65&quot;, oops. Everything works fine and the image is rendered correctly when I switch to JDK 7, which confirms my theory that the problem was AWT but it was a transient bug so we&apos;re good.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13987387" author="lehmi" created="Fri, 2 May 2014 06:12:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Closed after releasing PDFBox 1.8.5&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
